’Ł@43e041171efca85959d9ee73eefeb12a4264536fe6b9cdcec06baa727497bb1aŁŽTitle: title: job unfreeze
Path: Examples
Content:
Unfreeze the latest frozen job.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> job unfreeze


```
Unfreeze a specific frozen job by its PID.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> job unfreeze 4


```
’Ł@13918becaf6f314c2a6cb149897d28c1790f43121ecb117e01dc78ed13098cfaŁķTitle: title: job unfreeze
Path: Notes
Content:
When a running process is frozen (with the SIGTSTP signal or with the Ctrl-Z key on unix),

a background job gets registered for this process, which can then be resumed using this command.
